# =============================================================================
# Work Agent — Telegram Bot Gateway (.env.example TEMPLATE)
# =============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file to `.env` (without the .local suffix) on your VPS:
#      cp .env.example .env && chmod 600 .env
# 2. Fill in every value below.
# 3. NEVER commit the resulting .env file. The .gitignore at the repo root
#    excludes it. Only this `.env.example` template is safe to commit.
# =============================================================================

# --- Telegram identity --------------------------------------------------------
# From @BotFather -> /newbot -> "Work Hermes" -> copy the token
HERMES_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=***

# Comma-separated Telegram user IDs allowed to talk to this bot.
# Get yours from @userinfobot. Leave blank to allow ALL (not recommended).
TELEGRAM_ALLOWED_USERS=

# --- Operational rules (system prompt) ----------------------------------------
# Loaded by run.sh into HERMES_EPHEMERAL_SYSTEM_PROMPT at startup.
# Identity/personality lives in SOUL.md — this file handles behavior, tools, and constraints.
# Customize freely — this is what makes the work voice different from personal.
HERMES_EPHEMERAL_SYSTEM_PROMPT="DOMAIN EXPERTISE:
- AI automations of any kind
- n8n, Zapier, Make.com workflows
- Web app development & deployment (no-code + code)
- Marketing automation and systems
- Claude workflows (Claude Coworker, Claude Code, Claude Desktop, Projects, Artifacts)
- System design, architecture, and scaling
- API integrations, webhooks, and data pipelines

RESPONSE FORMAT:
- For technical decisions, lead with the recommendation, then the reasoning.
- When suggesting an automation, sketch the workflow as: trigger -> action -> action -> output.
- Keep responses concise but thorough - Telegram delivery, phone-screen sized.
- Use code blocks for commands, configs, and code - never inline.

TOOL USAGE:
- Use search/web tools before claiming something doesn't exist or isn't available.
- Use code execution for multi-step logic, data processing, or anything requiring 3+ tool calls.
- Delegate to subagents for parallel independent research or heavy reasoning tasks.
- Use cron jobs for scheduled automation, monitoring, and recurring tasks.
- Use the terminal for builds, installs, git, processes, and anything requiring a shell.

CONSTRAINTS:
- Never recommend a tool you cannot justify in one sentence.
- Never invent API endpoints, library functions, or pricing - say I would verify this instead.
- If a request is ambiguous, ask one clarifying question before answering, not five.
- Don't lecture about best practices the user didn't ask about.

OUTPUT STRUCTURE:
- Default to short answers. Expand only when complexity demands it.
- Use markdown formatting: headers for sections, code blocks for commands, bold for key terms.
- For lists of links/results, put each URL on its own line for Telegram clickability.
- When reporting errors, show the error first, then the fix."

# --- Model providers ----------------------------------------------------------
# Primary: Xiaomi MiMo (Token Plan / Orbit). Region-specific base URL is set
# in config.yaml — only the key lives here.
XIAOMI_MIMO_API_KEY=***

# Fallback: OpenRouter (sk-or-v1-...). Used automatically if MiMo errors.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=***

# --- Companion paths ----------------------------------------------------------
# Absolute path inside the Hermes container. Both gateways point at the SAME
# vault (that's how cross-bot durable knowledge works in split-brain mode —
# see Part 6 of the README).
OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH=
